Professor '''Carl J. Posy''' is an [[Israel]]i philosopher. He is a full professor in the Department of [[Philosophy]] at the [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]] in [[Jerusalem]], Israel.<ref name="huji">{{cite web| url=https://scholars.huji.ac.il/llcc/people/carl-posy | title=Carl Posy – PhD, Yale University, 1971 | work=People | publisher=[[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]] | location=Israel | accessdate=30 January 2018 }}</ref>
Carl Posy received his [[PhD degree]] from [[Yale University]] in the [[United States]] in 1971.<ref name="huji" />
Posy's areas of research interest include the [[philosophy of mathematics]], [[philosophical logic]], the [[history of philosophy]] (particularly [[Kant]] and his predecessors).<ref name="huji"/> His publications include:
* ''Kant’s Philosophy of Mathematics: Modern Essays'', [[Springer (publisher)|Springer]], 1992. {{ISBN|978-0-7923-1495-0}} * ''Computability: [[Alan Turing|Turing]], [[Kurt Gödel|Gödel]], [[Alonzo Church|Church]], and Beyond'' (with [[Jack Copeland]] and [[Oron Shagrir]]), [[MIT Press]], 2013. {{ISBN|978-0262527484}}.<ref name="mit-press">{{cite web| url=https://mitpress.mit.edu/authors/carl-j-posy | title=Carl J. Posy | publisher=[[MIT Press]] | accessdate=30 January 2018 }}</ref>
[[File:NLI building2.jpg|thumb|The [[National Library of Israel]] on the campus of the [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]], where Carl Posy was Academic Director<ref name="jpost" />]] Posy is a former Academic Director of the [[National Library of Israel]].<ref name="jpost">{{cite web| url=http://www.jpost.com/Israel/National-Library-to-be-established-in-Jerusalem | title=National Library to be Established in Jerusalem | first=Ehud Zion | last=Waldoks | date=27 November 2007 | newspaper=[[The Jerusalem Post]] | accessdate=30 January 2018 }}</ref><ref name="unc">{{cite web| url=https://sils.unc.edu/events/2012/carl-posy | title=Former Academic Director of the National Library of Israel to speak at UNC at Chapel Hill | publisher=[[University of North Carolina]] | date=2012 | accessdate=30 January 2018 }}</ref>
