{{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Radomir Konstantinović | image =Radomir Konstantinovic.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = Радомир Константиновић | native_name_lang = sr | birth_date = {{birth date|1928|03|27}} | birth_place = [[Subotica]], [[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2011|10|27|1928|03|27}} | death_place = [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]] | resting_place = | occupation = writer, philosopher | language = [[Serbo-Croatian]] | nationality = Yugoslavian/Serbian | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = <!-- or: | genres = --> | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = | notablework = ''Filosofija palanke'' | awards = {{awd|[[NIN Award]]|1960|Izlazak}} | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }} '''Radomir Konstantinović''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|Радомир Константиновић}}; 1928−2011) was [[Serbia]]n writer and philosopher. His most famous work is a philosophical [[treatise]] ''"Filosofija palanke"'' (''The small town philosophy'').<ref name=Novostidies>{{cite web|last1=N.|first1=V.|title=Preminuo Radomir Konstantinović|url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/kultura.71.html:351175-%D0%9F%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%B8%D0%BD%D1%83%D0%BE-%D0%A0%D0%B0%D0%B4%D0%BE%D0%BC%D0%B8%D1%80-%D0%9A%D0%BE%D0%BD%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B0%D0%BD%D1%82%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%9B|publisher=[[Vecernje novosti]]|accessdate=19 February 2015|language=Serbian|date=28 October 2011|trans-title=Radomir Konstantinović dies}}</ref> He won the prestigious literary [[NIN Award]] in 1960 for the novel ''"Izlazak"'' (''Exodus'').
==Biography== {{expand section|date=July 2018}} Konstantinović was born on 27 March 1928 in [[Subotica]].<ref name=Novostidies/> He started his literary career as a poet. He published a book of poetry ''"Kuće bez krova"'' (''A house without a roof'') in 1951, but then switched to writing novels and wrote a whole series of [[experimental novel]]s. His novel ''"Izlazak"'' (''Exodus'') won him the 1960 [[NIN Award]] for the best novel of the year.<ref name=winner>{{cite web|title=Dobitnik NIN-ove nagrade|url=http://www.b92.net/kultura/knjige/vesti.php?yyyy=2009&mm=01&nav_id=340604|publisher=[[B92]]|accessdate=19 February 2015|language=Serbian|date=22 January 2009|trans-title=Winner of the NIN Award|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150219224832/http://www.b92.net/kultura/knjige/vesti.php?yyyy=2009&mm=01&nav_id=340604|archivedate=19 February 2015|df=}}</ref> ''Radomir Konstantinović award'' is awarded every two years in his honour.
==Literary works== *''“Kuća bez krova”'' (''House without a roof'') — 1951, poetry book<ref name=cover>{{cite book|last1=Konstantinović|first1=Radomir|title=Filosofija palanke|date=2010|publisher=Otkrovenje|location=Belgrade|isbn=978-86-83353-52-1|page=book cover|language=Serbian}}</ref> *''"Daj nam danas"'' (''Give us today'') — 1954, novel *''"Mišolovka"'' (''Mouse trap'') — 1956, novel *''"Čisti i prljavi"'' (''The dirty and the clean'') — 1958, novel *''"Izlazak"'' (''Exodus'') — 1960, novel *''"Ahasfer ili traktat o pivskoj flaši"'' (''Ahafser or the treatise on the bear bottle'') — 1964, novel *''"Pentagram"'' — 1966, book of essays *''"Filosofija palanke"'' (''Small town philosophy'') — 1969, philosophical treatise *''"Biće i jezik"'' (''Being and language'') — 1983 *''"Dekartova smrt"'' (''The death of [[Descartes]]'') — 1996 *''"Beket prijatelj"'' (''Beckett friend'') — 2000, collection of letters [[Samuel Beckett]] sent to Konstantinović
